ðŸ§  What is File Handling?
File handling in Python allows you to store information permanently by interacting with files on disk (like .txt, .csv, etc.).

ðŸ“‚ Opening a File
Syntax:
file = open("filename.txt", "mode")

Mode	Description
r	    Read (default)
w	    Write (creates file if not exists, erases if exists)
a	    Append (adds content at the end)
x	    Create (throws error if file exists)
r+	    Read and write

